  "text": "The trajectory tracking controller proposed by [CITATION_1] is also based on VSC and an HGO. This controller prevents the peaking phenomena in the plant through the global saturation of the control signal. However, the results obtained loc. cit. guarantee only semi-global stability and the finite time convergence of the state of the tracking error equation to a residual set of order √ ε. In contrast, the results in Theorem 2 are stronger, i.e., global stability and exponential convergence of the error states to a residual set of order ε. On the other hand, the approach of [CITATION_2] ) also considers nonlinear plants.",
